      "side": 0,
      "message": "there is a little history to explain here, the \"-host-\" infix was used because, believe or not, these build files were parsed by the Android *platform* build a very long time ago, and this build generates Android and device-specific (e.g. ARM) by default. I.e. in this context, \"target\" binaries run on an Android device, and \"host\" binaries run on the developer\u0027s machine.\n\nThe emulator build is different now, but supports cross-compilation, in this context, \"target\" binaries run on the developer\u0027s machine (in case of a regular build), or on the targetted cross system (e.g. Windows when buiding on Linux with --mingw).\n\nLOCAL_HOST_MODULE is defined to true to indicate that one needs to generate binaries for the build machine (i.e. the \u0027host\u0027 in this context), but we can rename the functions emugl-begin-xxxx instead of emugl-begin-host-xxxx without worry.",
      "revId": "7371367055fd1a94386897c19a6f0a0861ede51e",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
